-- ALL America Latina Quarterly Transported Volume Rises 8.9%; Earnings Climb
-- B y   L a u r a   P r i c e
-- 2010-10-19T10:54:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-19/all-america-latina-quarterly-transported-volume-rises-8-9-earnings-climb.html
     Oct. 19 (Bloomberg) --  ALL America Latina Logistica SA  said
third-quarter total transported volume rose 8.9 percent and
 earnings  before interest, taxes, depreciation and amortization
rose 8.1 percent.  Transported volume at the Brazilian unit rose 9.6 percent
from a year earlier and Ebitda rose 6.5 percent, ALL said in a
regulatory filing today. The  company  says its perspectives for
the fourth quarter are “positive.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Price in London at 
 lprice3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
